{"parentUuid":"ef446448-3881-479a-9096-4eeed0f87f57","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a97f4764709b8dd41","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs1PNFSq7sFpYXBT2qt3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018Dd6YLY7XkZXiPugbHNufy","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cd \"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\" && ls .pipeline/ 2>/dev/null && echo --- && cat .pipeline/acceptance.md 2>/dev/null"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25781,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":267,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25781},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":267,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":25781,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":25781,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccs1PMCCi7hY8eYpNVAGK","attributionAgent":"testing","type":"assistant","uuid":"ba4b2027-07ed-4167-a8b5-4d34afd7df00","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:06:50.768Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"ef446448-3881-479a-9096-4eeed0f87f57","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"a97f4764709b8dd41","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UK618Yw6KE1YWWgVmetPWp","type":"tool_result","content":"On branch feature/usage-export\nChanges not staged for commit:\n  (use \"git add <file>...\" to update what will be committed)\n  (use \"git restore <file>...\" to discard changes in working directory)\n\tmodified:   PROJECT.md\n\tmodified:   docs/system_architecture.md\n\tmodified:   src/api/README.md\n\tmodified:   src/main.py\n\tmodified:   src/repositories/README.md\n\tmodified:   src/repositories/usage_repo.py\n\tmodified:   src/services/README.md\n\nUntracked files:\n  (use \"git add <file>...\" to include in what will be committed)\n\tsrc/api/csv_export.py\n\tsrc/api/routes/usage_export.py\n\tsrc/api/schemas/usage_export.py\n\tsrc/services/usage_export_service.py\n\ttests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py\n\ttests/integration/test_usage_export_perf.py\n\ttests/test_csv_export.py\n\ttests/test_schemas_usage_export.py\n\ttests/test_usage_export_service.py\n\nno changes added to commit (use \"git add\" and/or \"git commit -a\")\n---\n---\nfeature: usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\nbrief: PROJECT.md + .pipeline/requirements.md (authoritative)\nrun_type: revised (single allowed pass; addressed .pipeline/plan-audit.md material flags — see ## Revision notes)\nrepomix_pack_sha256: 67eadd304a8283772e6bc7833c535e9f4e6dfc088dcde667aac265fc0083de68\nrepomix_pack_files: 54\nrepomix_pack_tokens: 26820\ndesign_source: none (CSV API, no UI)\nmigration_added: false\ninfra_change: false\nnew_stored_data: false\ntest_strategy: pyramid\ntasks_file_emitted: false  # decomposition trigger under the CURRENT engine contract is the SINGLE >=25-estimated-files leg; the old >=15-criteria OR-leg was RETIRED. Estimated change set ~14 files is below 25, so no tasks.md. Criteria count (22) is not a decomposition trigger under the current contract.\n---\n\n# Plan — usage CSV export (`GET /v1/usage/export`)\n\n## Summary\n\nWe add one read-only endpoint, `GET /v1/usage/export`, that streams the authenticated\ncaller's own `usage_rollup` rows as an RFC 4180 CSV (`customer_id,metric,window_start,\ntotal_quantity`), with optional `customer_id` / `metric` / `from` / `to` filters, a hard\n100,000-row cap, and OWASP CSV-formula-injection escaping at the encoding boundary. The\ncore approach is a **streaming response backed by a PostgreSQL server-side cursor inside a\ntenant-scoped transaction**, chosen over buffering the whole result in memory because a\n100k-row export buffered per concurrent request is a cheap memory-exhaustion (DoS) vector,\nand over pagination because the brief scoped size control to \"row cap + filters, no\npagination this slice.\" The feature reuses every existing edge control (API-key auth,\nTier-2 per-key throttle, security headers, error envelope, structured logging, RLS\nbackstop) and reuses the exact validated identifier types the ingest/query paths already\nenforce — so it adds a new HTTP surface without a new auth mechanism, a new migration, or\nany change to the existing endpoints. It is intentionally isolated in new modules so the\nexisting `GET /v1/usage` code path is untouched (the brief's no-behavior-change constraint).\n\nThe authoritative brief (`.pipeline/requirements.md`) resolved nearly everything; its one\n`Open` item (the documented p95 target number) is carried below as Open Question 1 with a\nstated default (p95 < 500 ms at the cap). Everything in the brief's `Out of scope` list\n(pagination, admin-only gating, other formats/compression/async jobs, changes to existing\nendpoints, extra audit logging) is treated as a hard exclusion and not planned.\n\n## Stack notes\n\nThe feature sits entirely inside Meterly's existing stack; every default was assessed and\nkept — none swapped.\n\n- **Backend — Python 3.12 / FastAPI (kept).** The endpoint is one more FastAPI route on the\n  existing app; mirrors the proven `GET /v1/usage` composition. No reason to deviate.\n- **CSV encoding — Python stdlib `csv` (kept, and mandated by the brief).** *What:* use\n  `csv.writer` with an explicit RFC 4180 dialect. *Why over a hand-rolled encoder:* a\n  hand-rolled encoder is the classic source of quoting bugs (a value containing a comma,\n  quote, or embedded newline breaks a naive `\",\".join(...)`), and getting RFC 4180 quoting\n  exactly right is precisely what stdlib `csv` already does and is tested to do. *How:*\n  `csv.writer` with `lineterminator=\"\\r\\n\"` (RFC 4180 CRLF) and `QUOTE_MINIMAL` (quote only\n  fields containing comma/quote/CR/LF) writing into a per-row `io.StringIO` we drain and\n  reset each row — this reuses stdlib correctness while keeping constant memory (we never\n  hold more than one row's text). Formula-injection escaping is applied to text cells\n  *before* they reach the writer (see the CSV-encoding section).\n- **Data store — PostgreSQL (kept), read-only, no migration.** The export reads the\n  existing `usage_rollup` aggregate. No new table, column, index, or data-classification\n  surface — consistent with the brief's \"no new stored data.\" See Data section for the\n  ordering/index tradeoff this creates and why we still add no migration.\n- **Streaming — Starlette `StreamingResponse` + SQLAlchemy async `session.stream()` (new\n  use of an existing capability).** Assessed against buffering and against chunked keyset\n  pagination; the server-side-cursor-in-one-transaction option won on simplicity +\n  single-snapshot consistency. Full rationale in the Backend section.\n- **Auth — existing API-key facade (kept).** Any authenticated key may export its own\n  tenant's data (brief: not admin-gated). Reuses `require_api_key` + the Tier-2 per-key\n  throttle exactly as `GET /v1/usage` does.\n- **Observability / logging — structlog facade + CloudWatch/X-Ray/Sentry (kept).** One new\n  `usage.export` audit event through the existing `get_logger()` facade; no new SLO or\n  burn-rate alarm for this reporting slice (the binding perf criterion is a documented p95\n  sanity check, not an SLO — see Open Question 1).\n- **Infra / IaC — no change.** No provisioned resource is added; the route ships through the\n  existing CI → build-provenance → `deploy.yml` chain with no `infra/` edit. (The `infra/`\n  files marked modified in the working tree belong to earlier work on this branch, not this\n  feature.)\n\nNo default is being recommended against; nothing here needs a checkpoint override on stack\ngrounds.\n\n## Backend — route, service, repository\n\n### Route — `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (new module)\n\n*What:* a new router module exposing `GET /v1/usage/export`, registered in `src/main.py`.\n*Why a new module rather than adding to `src/api/routes/usage.py`:* the brief requires \"no\nbehavior change to any existing endpoint\"; putting the export in its own module keeps\n`usage.py` (which owns `GET /v1/usage`) literally untouched, making the no-change guarantee\ntrivially auditable in the diff, and matches the existing per-resource module convention\n(`events.py`, `usage.py`, `quotas.py`). *How:* it reuses the same sibling dependency the\nother routes use to pin ordering —\n\n- `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` (auth `require_api_key` → Tier-2 per-key throttle,\n  in that order) — copied as a sibling, not imported, per the established convention that\n  each route's dependency chain stays independently readable. No admin-scope gate (any\n  authenticated key may export — brief resolved).\n\nThe handler is deliberately two-phase to make the row cap a clean pre-body 422:\n\n1. **Pre-flight cap check (still a normal request, can 422 cleanly).** Call the service's","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"be022a86-ab7e-49cd-9758-7ae26112f825","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:06:53.491Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ef446448-3881-479a-9096-4eeed0f87f57","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
{"parentUuid":"ba4b2027-07ed-4167-a8b5-4d34afd7df00","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ed4149fd-c5a8-4db4-bdd2-38a556acc251","agentId":"a97f4764709b8dd41","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018Dd6YLY7XkZXiPugbHNufy","type":"tool_result","content":"acceptance.md\narchive\nast-grep.err\nasvs-sast.err\nasvs-sast.json\ndast-budget.json\ndast.env\ngitleaks.err\ngitleaks.json\nimplementation-progress.md\nlockfile.err\nloop-events.jsonl\nloop-state.json\nosv.err\nosv.json\nplan-approved\nplan-audit.md\nplan.md\nrepomix-pack.xml\nrequirements.md\nrun-log.jsonl\nsbom.cdx.json\nsbom.err\nscan-log.jsonl\nscan-reconciliation.json\nsecurity-report.md\nsecurity-status.json\nsemgrep.err\nsemgrep.json\nsmoke-status.json\nsmoke.env\nstate.json\nsurface-delta.md\n---\n---\nfeature: usage CSV export (GET /v1/usage/export)\ncriteria_total: 22\ndelegated_criteria: [AC18]\nderived_from: PROJECT.md + .pipeline/requirements.md (resolved items) + STRIDE + input-surface + DAST-readiness\nnotes: >\n  Feature-level definition-of-done. Implementation builds to these; testing maps each ID to a\n  test (criteria_covered). AC18 is delegated to the security stage (ASVS reconciliation), so\n  testing marks it covered:false, delegated:\"security\". No performance k6 load AC: the export is\n  a reporting route with a documented p95 sanity check (AC16); the binding perf constraint is the\n  negative one (AC15 — existing endpoints/budgets untouched). AC22 (added in the revision pass)\n  covers the pre-flight safe-error shape — distinct from plan §R3, which only accepts the\n  post-200 mid-stream truncation case.\n---\n\n| ID | Criterion | File / layer | How verified |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| AC1 | Response is RFC 4180 CSV via stdlib `csv`: header row exactly `customer_id,metric,window_start,total_quantity` (brief column order), CRLF line endings, fields containing comma/quote/newline quoted | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit (dialect, header, CRLF, quoting) + integration end-to-end body assertion |\n| AC2 | Optional `customer_id`/`metric`/`from`/`to` filters applied (reusing existing allowlist types + window bounds); all omitted → full supported range | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Unit (schema) + integration (each filter narrows the row set; none → all caller rows) |\n| AC3 | `from`/`to` validation: timezone-aware, `from <= to`, both within `[now-90d, now+1h]`, naive datetime rejected | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py` | Unit (accept/reject cases incl. naive, inverted range, out-of-window) |\n| AC4 | Input validation (non-waivable): malformed / wrong-type / unknown / out-of-range query param → 422 `validation_failed`; `extra=\"forbid\"` rejects unknown params | `src/api/schemas/usage_export.py`, `src/api/errors.py` | Unit + integration (422 envelope with `code=validation_failed`) |\n| AC5 | Rate limit: post-auth **Tier-2 per-`api_key_id`** throttle applies (principal-keyed); two principals on one client IP get independent buckets | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` (reuses `src/auth/rate_limit.py`) | Integration two-principals-one-IP discriminating test |\n| AC6 | Authorization: any authenticated key (ingest or admin) may export; unauthenticated/invalid → 401; no scope gate | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/auth` | Integration (ingest key 200, admin key 200, no/invalid key 401) |\n| AC7 | Tenant isolation: export returns ONLY the caller's `api_key_id` rows; two tenants' data never cross (explicit `api_key_id` filter is the primary control; RLS is backstop) | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration two-tenant test (tenant A's export excludes tenant B's rows) |\n| AC8 | Row cap: a result exceeding 100,000 rows → 422 `validation_failed` (\"narrow filters\"), **no partial body streamed** (pre-flight count before any response byte) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (>100k rows → 422, response body is the envelope not CSV) |\n| AC9 | Streaming constant memory: rows streamed as read via a server-side cursor, response not fully buffered before send | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration streaming-not-buffered sanity (first bytes observable before generator exhausted / bounded memory on a large export) |\n| AC10 | CSV formula-injection escape: text cells (`customer_id`,`metric`) starting with `= + - @ \\t \\r` prefixed with `'`; control chars neutralized; numeric/timestamp cells untouched | `src/api/csv_export.py` | Unit (incl. leading-`-` `customer_id`, each trigger, control chars, numeric/timestamp unaffected) + integration end-to-end |\n| AC11 | Response headers: `Content-Type: text/csv; charset=utf-8`; `Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=usage-export-<UTC timestamp>.csv` (no tenant identifier in filename); inherits `nosniff` + `Cache-Control: no-store` | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py`, `src/api/middleware.py` | Integration header assertions (incl. filename pattern, no tenant id) |\n| AC12 | Empty result → 200 header-only CSV (single header row, zero data rows), never 404 | `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Integration (caller with no matching rollups → 200, one CSV line) |\n| AC13 | Deterministic ordering `ORDER BY window_start, customer_id, metric ASC`; identical exports are byte-stable | `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration (asserts row order over a seeded multi-row set) |\n| AC14 | Value formats: `window_start` as UTC ISO-8601 with offset (identical to JSON response form); `total_quantity` as `str(Decimal)` (plain decimal, no scientific notation) | `src/api/csv_export.py`, `src/services/usage_export_service.py` | Unit + integration (format assertions) |\n| AC15 | No behavior change: `POST /v1/events`, `GET /v1/usage`, `PUT /v1/quotas` behavior/budgets/tests unchanged; no new Alembic revision / migration added | repo-wide (negative) | Existing test suites pass unchanged; no new file under `alembic/versions/` |\n| AC16 | Performance budget: export route **p95 < 500 ms at the 100,000-row cap** (documented target, integration timing sanity — NOT a k6 load AC) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py` | Integration timing sanity test at ~100k rows |\n| AC17 | Audit logging: exactly one `usage.export` `info` event at completion (`userId`=opaque `api_key_id`, `operation`, `rowCount`, `capped`, `completed`, filter-presence booleans — no raw `customer_id`); over-cap request logged at `warn` | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/logging` | Unit/integration (log fields present, no PII, one event; `warn` on over-cap) |\n| AC18 | ASVS 5.0 L1/L2 controls for the triggered chapters (V1/V2/V4/V6/V8/V13/V14/V16) present across the change set; recorded waivers honored | cross-cutting | Delegated to security stage (`delegated:\"security\"`) — reconciled against plan §ASVS Compliance |\n| AC19 (DAST-1) | Served OpenAPI schema includes `GET /v1/usage/export` with its `200 text/csv` and `422` responses, matching the implemented route (not hand-drifted) | `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Integration (assert route + responses present in `/openapi.json`) |\n| AC20 (DAST-2) | A seeded non-production DAST test key (reuse the existing seeded key; credentials from env/secrets, never hardcoded) can call the export | `scripts/seed_api_key.py` (existing), test fixtures | Integration (seeded key successfully hits the export in staging/local) |\n| AC21 (DAST-3) | Auth-context recorded for scanners: `Authorization: Bearer mtr_live_<key_id>_<secret>` header shape, documented in the plan and exercised by the integration auth path | plan §Auth, `src/auth/api_key.py` (existing) | Documented in plan + integration test uses this exact Bearer shape |\n| AC22 | Safe-error / fail-closed pre-flight: a forced internal error during the pre-flight `prepare_export` `COUNT` phase (before any response byte) returns the generic `500 internal` error-envelope (no stack/SQL/internal path leaked), rolls back the transaction, and starts **no** stream / emits **no** partial CSV body (ASVS 16.5.x). Distinct from plan §R3 (post-200 mid-stream truncation, accepted) | `src/services/usage_export_service.py`, `src/api/errors.py`, `src/api/routes/usage_export.py` | Unit in `tests/test_usage_export_service.py` (non-cap DB error propagates, not swallowed, no stream started) + integration in `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (forced pre-flight `COUNT` error → `500 internal` envelope, no leak, no partial body) |","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"1e43b7ef-3fc8-4632-ba5f-47d2caaa5635","timestamp":"2026-07-09T19:06:54.078Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ba4b2027-07ed-4167-a8b5-4d34afd7df00","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"d6fd840f-4c15-4ec4-8e2b-f4a42b2cbb1a","version":"2.1.204","gitBranch":"feature/usage-export"}
