{"parentUuid":"0f470d7c-d587-4f64-af19-cb5384992c2d","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a97f4764709b8dd41","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011Ccs2uLBdXSKuxtBL5PAN6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I've completed the testing pass on the `usage-export` feature branch. Summary:\n\n**Passing tests:** 180 passed, 0 failed (4 k6-load tests deselected — verified this session via `which k6` that no k6 binary is on PATH in this sandbox; those tests exercise `POST /v1/events`/`GET /v1/usage` under load, unrelated to this feature).\n\n**Added this session** (gaps implementation left):\n- `tests/test_usage_export_service.py::test_prepare_export_passes_when_exactly_at_cap_boundary` — the missing boundary case (count exactly == 100,000 must pass, not just count > cap rejects).\n- `tests/integration/test_usage_export_endpoint.py::test_export_seeded_dast_key_can_call_the_export` — AC20 required \"a seeded DAST key can call the export,\" but the pre-existing `test_seed_api_key_script.py` only proved the script persists a working key row, never actually called an endpoint with it. Closed that gap.\n\n**Coverage:** combined lines 91%, **branches 66%** (functions not tracked — coverage.py has no function-granularity metric). The low branch figure is entirely pre-existing debt outside this diff (`src/observability/sentry.py` 24%, `src/services/events_service.py` 69%, `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py`/`events_repo.py`/`api_keys_repo.py` in the 60-70s) — every file this feature touches or adds (`csv_export.py`, `routes/usage_export.py`, `schemas/usage_export.py`, `services/usage_export_service.py`) is at 100% branch coverage; `usage_repo.py`'s extension is 88% combined, dragged down mostly by one pre-existing untested `None` branch in the untouched `find_usage_rollup`.\n\n**Shape:** pyramid as declared — 116 unit / 64 integration / 0 e2e (backend-only feature).\n\n**Acceptance criteria: 20/22 covered**, 1 delegated, 1 genuinely uncovered:\n- **AC18** delegated to security per `acceptance.md` frontmatter — correct, not invented.\n- **AC16 (perf budget) left uncovered, not silently passed.** I re-measured the p95 timing test myself this session: real p95 at the 100,000-row cap is **25,210 ms** against the documented 500 ms budget — about 50x over. This independently corroborates (worse than) implementation's own disclosed ~9.8s finding on different hardware. The test intentionally doesn't hard-assert the budget (plan left it as an open/unconfirmed number), but a budget missed by this margin is a real, reproducible defect, not a passing criterion — I recorded `perf.status: fail` with `perf.scenario` populated (never left null) and marked AC16 `covered: false` with the measured numbers as the reason, per the criterion-completeness rule. This should route to debugging/checkpoint, not ship silently.\n\n**CI coverage floor filled** (ledger M4-1): `.github/workflows/pipeline-ci.yml` still had `<COVERAGE_FLOOR>` — filled from CLAUDE.md's done-bar (`>= 85%`) as `--cov-fail-under=85`.\n\n**Test quality (advisory, `.pipeline/test-quality.json`):** `quality_ok: false`. Mutation testing could not run — verified this session via `mutmut --version`, which refuses on native Windows (matches the project's own CI comment deferring mutation to the Linux job). Adversarial gaps recorded: AC16's real perf defect (high), AC9's chunk-count proxy not directly measuring peak memory (medium), a few low-severity combinatorial/disconnect-path gaps.\n\nFiles touched/created this session:\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\test_usage_export_service.py` (added boundary test)\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_usage_export_endpoint.py` (added AC20 test)\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.github\\workflows\\pipeline-ci.yml` (filled coverage floor)\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\